{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1827", "title": "Small claims court: jurisdiction.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Smallclaimscourt", "jurisdiction"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law establishes a small claims division, known as a small claims court, in each superior court. Existing law provides that the small claims court has jurisdiction over actions seeking certain forms of relief, including money damages in specified amounts and claims brought by natural persons, not exceeding $12,500, except as specified. Existing law prohibits a person from filing more than 2 small claims actions in any calendar year in which the amount demanded exceeds $2,500, except as specified.\n\nThis bill would increase the small claims court jurisdiction over actions brought by a natural person, except as specified, and other specified actions within the jurisdiction of the small claims court if the amount does not exceed $15,000. The bill would also allow a person to file no more than 3 small claims actions, as specified, in any calendar year."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1827"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-11", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 14.", "date": "2026-02-12", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on JUD.", "date": "2026-02-23", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on JUD.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee chair, with author's amendments: Amend, and re-refer to Com. on